comment_data.body:
Nice.

One little bit-pick: If you define the whole block in a `.proto` section like this, then it will end up before the user code in the generated `.c` file, next to the other pre-declarations. Please only define this signature prototype in that section to make it globally available, and move the implementation into a normal `PySetContains` section (without suffix), so that the helper function itself goes to a less user visible place at the end of the file.

Almost. ;)
I really just meant that this one signature should go into the `.proto` section. All the rest can go into the implementation, also the `...Unhashable` function. Since the latter is not called by user generated code but only by the global `...ContainsTF` helper function that *follows* it, there is no need to pre-declare it.
Ok, I had miunserstood. This should now be fixed.
